### readBBAddrMap() {#afd20ce2ce3ff93c0b9e858b5bda86c85}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::vector&lt; BBAddrMap &gt; &gt; ELFObjectFileBase::readBBAddrMap (std::optional&lt; unsigned &gt; TextSectionIndex=std::nullopt, std::vector&lt; <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/object/pgoanalysismap">PGOAnalysisMap</a> &gt; &#42; PGOAnalyses=nullptr) const</>}>
Returns a vector of all BB address maps in the object file.

When <code>TextSectionIndex</code> is specified, only returns the BB address maps corresponding to the section with that index. When <code>PGOAnalyses</code>is specified (PGOAnalyses is not nullptr), the vector is cleared then filled with extra PGO data. <code>PGOAnalyses</code> will always be the same length as the return value when it is requested assuming no error occurs. Upon failure, <code>PGOAnalyses</code> will be emptied.

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/elfobjectfile-h/#l00124">124</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/object/elfobjectfile-h">ELFObjectFile.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/object/elfobjectfile-cpp/#l01013">1013</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/object/elfobjectfile-cpp">ELFObjectFile.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
